issue.title: Only works with AsyncOpenAI client, not synchronous OpenAI client
issue.body:
Tested in Jupyter Notebook with openpipe-art[backend]==0.4.7 as well as by using 2048.ipynb in colab.
If you replace "from openai import AsyncOpenAI" with "from openai import OpenAI", "AsyncOpenAI" with "OpenAI" and "await client.chat.completions.create" with "client.chat.completions.create" in the rollout cell of 2048.ipynb, training cell will freeze permanently.
It matters, because some agentic frameworks like [Qwen-Agent](https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen-Agent) use synchronous OpenAI client. Therefore, it's impossible use Qwen-Agent with ART TrainableModel endpoints.
I have not managed to find any workaround yet. I would also appreciate any feedback if I‚Äôm doing something wrong.

comment.body: Yep, executing Qwen-Agent with "await asyncio.to_thread" indeed works. So, I guess this is solved. Thanks, @bradhilton

pull_request.title: Fix SQL question navigation button states by correcting index calculation
pull_request.body:
Fixed incorrect navigation button states in SQL questions where buttons were using 1-based question IDs instead of 0-based array indices.

## Problem
The navigation buttons had incorrect enabled/disabled states:
- Question 1: Previous button was enabled (should be disabled)
- Question 25: Next button was disabled (should be enabled) 
- Question 26: Next button was enabled (should be disabled)

## Root Cause
The `QuestionNavigation` component was designed to work with 0-based array indices (0-25), but was receiving 1-based question IDs (1-26) from the SQL page component.

```vue
<!-- QuestionNavigation.vue logic -->
:disabled="index === 0"                    // Expected 0-based index
:disabled="index === questionsLength - 1"  // Expected 0-based index

<!-- But was receiving 1-based question IDs -->
:index="index"  // This was question ID (1-26), not array index (0-25)
```

## Solution
Added a computed property `currentQuestionIndex` that converts 1-based question IDs to 0-based array indices:

```javascript
const currentQuestionIndex = computed(() => {
    // Convert 1-based question ID to 0-based array index for navigation
    if (questions.value.length === 0 || index.value === 0) {
        return 0; // Return 0 as default when questions haven't loaded yet
    }
    
    const availableIds = questions.value.map(q => q.id).sort((a, b) => a - b);
    const computedIndex = availableIds.indexOf(index.value);
    return computedIndex >= 0 ? computedIndex : 0;
});
```

Updated the template to pass the correct index:
```vue
<SqlQuestionContent 
    :index="currentQuestionIndex"  <!-- Changed from index to currentQuestionIndex -->
    :questions-length="questions.length"
    @prev="prevQuestion"
    @next="nextQuestion"
/>
```

## Verification
Console logs confirmed correct index calculation:
- Question 1: `computedIndex: 0` ‚Üí Previous disabled ‚úÖ, Next enabled ‚úÖ
- Question 25: `computedIndex: 24` ‚Üí Previous enabled ‚úÖ, Next enabled ‚úÖ  
- Question 26: `computedIndex: 25` ‚Üí Previous enabled ‚úÖ, Next disabled ‚úÖ

<screenshot>
![Question 1 with correct navigation states](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eabc4944-b056-48ae-b0f2-0c1663c41756)
</screenshot>

The fix ensures navigation buttons correctly reflect the user's position in the question sequence and prevents navigation beyond the valid range.
